WEBVTT

00:06.308 --> 00:08.571
<i>- Previously</i>
<i>on "New Amsterdam"...</i>

00:08.671 --> 00:10.733
<i>[tender music]</i>

00:10.833 --> 00:12.695
<i>- Dr. Helen Sharpe</i>
<i>is here in New York City</i>

00:12.795 --> 00:15.859
<i>representing the NHS'</i>
<i>fight against cancer.</i>

00:15.959 --> 00:21.005
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:23.567 --> 00:25.109
- Did you know she was
in New York?

00:25.209 --> 00:26.671
- No, not until
I saw her on TV.

00:26.771 --> 00:28.353
- I wish I could
have seen your face.

00:28.453 --> 00:29.394
It's not funny, all right?

00:29.494 --> 00:30.475
Elizabeth did see my face.

00:30.575 --> 00:31.436
Did she take a video?

00:31.536 --> 00:32.718
No, she didn't.

00:32.818 --> 00:33.999
Let's just say it
wasn't the best

00:34.099 --> 00:35.401
way to start a relationship.

00:35.501 --> 00:36.642
Wait, you and Elizabeth?

00:36.742 --> 00:39.245
- Almost, until I saw
Helen and basically

00:39.345 --> 00:41.568
frickin' short circuited,
which I'm sure

00:41.668 --> 00:43.730
is what every woman wants
in a prospective boyfriend.

00:43.830 --> 00:46.133
- Did you think that we'd still
be boyfriends at this age?

00:46.233 --> 00:47.214
No, I did not.

00:47.314 --> 00:48.415
Yeah. So you gonna see Helen?

00:48.515 --> 00:50.458
I don't know. Yes. No. Maybe.

00:50.558 --> 00:52.220
I--she hasn't even
reached out, OK?

00:52.320 --> 00:53.301
I don't even know
if it's on the table.

00:53.401 --> 00:54.422
- You're not even
a little bit curious?

00:54.522 --> 00:55.744
- Of cour--which part?

00:55.844 --> 00:57.225
- I mean, if she still
has feelings for you.

00:57.325 --> 00:59.508
If some part of her wishes
she could take it all back.

00:59.608 --> 01:01.190
I mean, what if she came back
to New York for a reason?

01:01.290 --> 01:02.431
I know, I know, but I can't.

01:02.531 --> 01:03.873
I can't be curious, OK?

01:03.973 --> 01:07.477
Not about any of it, because
I can't open that door.

01:07.577 --> 01:08.999
I can't fall back
into something that I

01:09.099 --> 01:10.520
worked so hard to get over.

01:10.620 --> 01:13.083
I just need to find
Elizabeth, apologise,

01:13.183 --> 01:15.546
make this right, OK?

01:20.912 --> 01:21.813
Hey.

01:21.913 --> 01:22.934
Hi.

01:23.034 --> 01:24.816
Hi.

01:24.916 --> 01:26.098
Hi.

01:26.198 --> 01:27.940
[phone buzzing]

01:28.040 --> 01:29.181
911.

01:29.281 --> 01:32.665
And I have a coffee 911.

01:32.765 --> 01:36.950
- Um, you know what, would
you mind interpreting for me,

01:37.050 --> 01:38.432
because I'm just a
little more clear when

01:38.532 --> 01:40.634
I'm not using the
wrong words, or, uh,

01:40.734 --> 01:42.856
unintentionally swearing.

01:44.979 --> 01:46.441
- Max, please do
not include Ben

01:46.541 --> 01:49.464
in our private conversations.

01:51.106 --> 01:53.749
[mouthing words]

01:57.273 --> 01:59.495
Oh, thank God.

01:59.595 --> 02:01.597
Thank you.

02:03.640 --> 02:06.042
[siren blares]

02:07.404 --> 02:10.568
[mouthing words]

02:17.976 --> 02:20.879
<i>[somber music]</i>

02:20.979 --> 02:27.867
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:12.317 --> 03:14.319
Hmm.

03:16.762 --> 03:18.764
[phone chimes]

03:21.527 --> 03:24.351
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

03:24.451 --> 03:31.538
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:35.703 --> 03:37.085
- So, this is my emergency,
huh?

03:37.185 --> 03:39.848
- Oh, it's urgent,
Dr. Reynolds.

03:39.948 --> 03:41.930
- Come here.
- Mm.

03:42.030 --> 03:44.032
Mmm.

03:46.435 --> 03:47.897
I can't believe it.

03:47.997 --> 03:50.860
One more week before
you have to go.

03:50.960 --> 03:54.264
- That is the beauty
of dating a travelling nurse.

03:54.364 --> 03:55.425
- Mm-hmm.

03:55.525 --> 03:57.147
What is that?

03:57.247 --> 04:00.591
Less time, and more heat.

04:00.691 --> 04:03.755
[banging on door]

04:03.855 --> 04:05.557
I might have a meeting.

04:05.657 --> 04:07.479
Do you have a meeting?

04:07.579 --> 04:09.882
I can't remember right now.

04:09.982 --> 04:11.984
OK.

04:15.588 --> 04:17.010
Manny?

04:17.110 --> 04:18.611
- There's the guy that
sliced into the phrenic nerve

04:18.711 --> 04:19.893
in anatomy lab.

04:19.993 --> 04:21.735
- No, no, that's only
'cause the cadaver shook

04:21.835 --> 04:23.096
when you dropped
that slice of pizza

04:23.196 --> 04:24.178
in the abdominal cavity.

04:24.278 --> 04:25.659
- What's up, man?
- It's been a minute.

04:25.759 --> 04:27.461
- Yeah, too many.
Too many.

04:27.561 --> 04:29.223
How you doing?
You look good.

04:29.323 --> 04:30.625
What are you doing here?

04:30.725 --> 04:32.507
It's my son.

04:32.607 --> 04:34.689
He's in the ICU.

04:36.772 --> 04:37.873
[monitor beeping]

04:37.973 --> 04:40.716
It's a fusiform aneurysm

04:40.816 --> 04:42.198
in the vertebral basilar
artery,

04:42.298 --> 04:44.580
very close to
the Circle of Willis.

04:46.262 --> 04:47.924
- That's deep in the base
of the brain, yes?

04:48.024 --> 04:48.845
Yes.

04:48.945 --> 04:50.407
Yes, where the blood travels.

04:50.507 --> 04:53.851
But the aneurysm
can blow any minute.

04:53.951 --> 04:56.894
Manny, we need
to operate immediately.

04:56.994 --> 04:58.817
I've called Dr. Emilio Nieves.

04:58.917 --> 05:02.020
He is the best neurosurgeon
on the East Coast.

05:02.120 --> 05:04.903
- You know how delicate cutting
into that part of the brain is.

05:05.003 --> 05:08.147
Slightest vibration,
my boy's own heartbeat

05:08.247 --> 05:09.869
could throw Nieves off
by a millimetre

05:09.969 --> 05:11.110
- and he could never wake up.
- Right. Right.

05:11.210 --> 05:13.473
But that's not going
to happen, OK?

05:13.573 --> 05:15.235
I'm going to stop
Manny Jr.'s heart

05:15.335 --> 05:16.917
before Nieves starts.

05:17.017 --> 05:19.360
We're going to get his body
temp down to 45 degrees,

05:19.460 --> 05:20.881
put him in cold plegia.

05:20.981 --> 05:23.364
All right, suspended animation.
All right?

05:23.464 --> 05:25.807
That way there's no pulse
to throw Nieves off

05:25.907 --> 05:27.889
as he makes the incision
to reconstruct

05:27.989 --> 05:31.333
the basilar artery using
an internal mammary artery.

05:31.433 --> 05:35.177
And when he's done,
I'll rewarm your son's body,

05:35.277 --> 05:38.902
restart his heart,
and everyone goes home.

05:39.002 --> 05:43.126
- Hearing it as a doctor,
it makes sense.

05:44.848 --> 05:47.071
- But when it's your child--
- Hey.

05:47.171 --> 05:51.175
I still owe you for totalling
that '66 Dodge Dart.

05:53.137 --> 05:55.140
Don't I?

05:56.982 --> 05:58.564
Let me make it up to you.

05:58.664 --> 06:01.327
<i>[somber music]</i>

06:01.427 --> 06:02.448
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:02.548 --> 06:04.090
Dr. Dyson, exactly how long

06:04.190 --> 06:05.371
do you and your team need
for this?

06:05.471 --> 06:06.933
- A quarter of New Amsterdam's
thallium allotment

06:07.033 --> 06:08.255
is unaccounted for, Dr. Bloom.

06:08.355 --> 06:09.896
- Right, and I'm not
trying to diminish

06:09.996 --> 06:11.819
the severity of a missing
radioactive element.

06:11.919 --> 06:14.101
But my ED is clean,
and my mood is bad,

06:14.201 --> 06:16.584
so I would appreciate
a real measure of time.

06:16.684 --> 06:19.908
Uh, as long as it takes.

06:20.008 --> 06:21.750
- 50-year-old male,
hypotensive,

06:21.850 --> 06:22.991
experiencing
shortness of breath

06:23.091 --> 06:24.713
due to multiple bee stings.

06:24.813 --> 06:26.715
- Oh, damn it, Dave.
- You know him?

06:26.815 --> 06:28.798
- Yeah, only because this is
his third time here this week.

06:28.898 --> 06:30.319
He's in anaphylactic shock.

06:30.419 --> 06:31.721
- Yeah, I was
transferring a beehive,

06:31.821 --> 06:32.962
and the cover ripped
for some reason.

06:33.062 --> 06:33.983
- Maybe because
you're an accountant.

06:34.063 --> 06:35.285
That's what I do.

06:35.385 --> 06:37.487
Who I am is an
urban outdoorsman.

06:37.587 --> 06:39.169
[coughing]

06:39.269 --> 06:41.292
- OK, let's get him
on 250 milligrams

06:41.392 --> 06:43.254
of hydrocortisone
and 50 milligrams of Benadryl.

06:43.354 --> 06:45.176
- My eye feels like
it's on fire.

06:45.276 --> 06:46.497
Ahh! Ahh!

06:46.597 --> 06:47.899
- There's a stinger in
the inner canthal region.

06:47.999 --> 06:49.100
[shouting in pain]

06:49.200 --> 06:50.302
- Dave, I need you
to stay still.

06:50.402 --> 06:51.543
- I don't like things
in my eye.

06:51.643 --> 06:53.185
- Then you should stop
leaving your office, hey?

06:53.285 --> 06:55.267
Hold him still.
Max, Max, uh--

06:55.367 --> 06:57.870
- Yeah, I got it. I got it.
- Hold him still.

06:57.970 --> 07:00.914
[shouting in pain]

07:01.014 --> 07:02.636
- Got it.
- That was fast.

07:02.736 --> 07:04.998
OK, let's take him to Bay 24,

07:05.098 --> 07:06.480
and let's monitor him
for the rest of the day.

07:06.580 --> 07:07.962
Got it.

07:08.062 --> 07:09.203
- No, wait!
No, stop!

07:09.303 --> 07:11.325
- I can't be here all day.
- Why not?

07:11.425 --> 07:13.888
- I'm taking my employees
on a Great Escape.

07:13.988 --> 07:16.651
- Sure, as long as it's
in Bay 24, that's fine.

07:16.751 --> 07:19.054
- Sorry, Great Escape?
What is that?

07:19.154 --> 07:21.377
- Day-long team-building trips
that take New Yorkers

07:21.477 --> 07:23.699
off the grid and up a mountain
for an eye-opening escape

07:23.799 --> 07:25.501
from city life
and city problems.

07:25.601 --> 07:28.024
The tickets are also expensive
and non-refundable.

07:28.124 --> 07:29.546
Yeah, I'll take them.

07:29.646 --> 07:31.668
I'll take all of them.

07:31.768 --> 07:34.511
Fine, but I only do Zelle.

07:34.611 --> 07:36.614
[coughs]

07:37.294 --> 07:39.197
- You won't even do
patio seating

07:39.297 --> 07:40.798
at a four-star restaurant
and now you want

07:40.898 --> 07:42.160
to venture off into the wild?

07:42.260 --> 07:43.802
- I just think it'd be nice
to spend a day

07:43.902 --> 07:46.164
outdoors with my friends
and my coworkers, right?

07:46.264 --> 07:48.487
- Hm, this is because Helen's
back in New York, isn't it?

07:48.587 --> 07:50.169
- No, no, no, I just want
to spend more time

07:50.269 --> 07:52.131
with the people
who are actually in my life.

07:52.231 --> 07:54.854
And after everything that
you have been going through,

07:54.954 --> 07:56.956
wouldn't that be nice?

07:59.639 --> 08:02.863
Brunstetter, page Candelario.

08:02.963 --> 08:05.706
<i>[rhythmic music]</i>

08:05.806 --> 08:07.809
- That's what
I'm talking about.

08:09.170 --> 08:11.713
Great idea, two words.

08:11.813 --> 08:13.195
[mouths words]

08:13.295 --> 08:14.717
- Cape Cod.
- Nope.

08:14.817 --> 08:17.440
Corporate retreat.

08:17.540 --> 08:18.841
That is very different.

08:18.941 --> 08:20.243
- It is very different,
but everything

08:20.343 --> 08:22.325
is packed and prepared
and ready to go

08:22.425 --> 08:23.927
so that we can have
some food, some fun,

08:24.027 --> 08:26.930
and maybe a little adventure.

08:27.030 --> 08:28.412
Max, I have appointments.

08:28.512 --> 08:29.934
- That's why I've got
substitute doctors who

08:30.034 --> 08:31.575
can step in at
a moment's notice

08:31.675 --> 08:34.419
so that we can take a day
to remember what truly matters.

08:34.519 --> 08:36.741
Plus, we'll probably
spend some time in a, uh,

08:36.841 --> 08:38.143
[clears throat]

08:38.243 --> 08:40.906
Tent, so maybe we could,
uh, you know,

08:41.006 --> 08:42.868
do important doctor stuff.

08:42.968 --> 08:44.970
- I'll go.
- Sorry.

08:46.012 --> 08:48.174
So what do you think?

08:51.177 --> 08:52.799
[mouthing words]

08:52.899 --> 08:54.641
- [whispering] Yes!
Thank you.

08:54.741 --> 08:56.563
Value of shared assets.

08:56.663 --> 08:57.765
Division of property.

08:57.865 --> 08:59.447
Child custody rights.

08:59.547 --> 09:03.091
I guess divorce comes down
to these little sticky notes.

09:03.191 --> 09:06.054
<i>[somber music]</i>

09:06.154 --> 09:13.182
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:13.282 --> 09:15.184
- Hey, buddy, you want
to climb a mountain?

09:15.284 --> 09:16.666
Yes.

09:16.766 --> 09:18.628
Thank you. Thank you.

09:18.728 --> 09:20.791
That was easy.

09:20.891 --> 09:23.474
Throw on a backpack, amigo,
because I am taking you

09:23.574 --> 09:24.715
to climb a mountain.

09:24.815 --> 09:26.517
I guess Helen texted you.

09:26.617 --> 09:28.479
She did.

09:28.579 --> 09:30.361
I don't know if I want
to see her, though.

09:30.461 --> 09:32.484
I don't even know if I want
to be in the same city as her.

09:32.584 --> 09:34.366
- 'Cause you don't want
to be tempted?

09:34.466 --> 09:35.567
It's like this.

09:35.667 --> 09:37.329
I just found out Luna
has a peanut allergy,

09:37.429 --> 09:39.652
so naturally I purge
the whole house of all peanuts,

09:39.752 --> 09:42.095
all peanut butter, because even
though she knows that it could

09:42.195 --> 09:44.698
make her stop breathing,
she still loves it,

09:44.798 --> 09:46.500
and she probably always will.

09:46.600 --> 09:49.263
So the only thing to do is
to remove it completely

09:49.363 --> 09:51.225
so it doesn't, you know,
kill her.

09:51.325 --> 09:52.827
[sighs] Yeah, yeah.

09:52.927 --> 09:54.829
Max, look, I got a big surgery
so I'm going to have to pass,

09:54.929 --> 09:57.031
but I understand
and fully support you

09:57.131 --> 09:58.673
getting the hell out of here.

09:58.773 --> 10:00.395
Thanks, buddy.

10:00.495 --> 10:02.497
[phone chimes]

10:03.779 --> 10:05.781
You going to get that?

10:06.902 --> 10:08.945
[phone chimes]

10:16.433 --> 10:17.534
Max.

10:17.634 --> 10:19.176
Get out of those scrubs.

10:19.276 --> 10:20.818
Get ready for
the Great Escape, right?

10:20.918 --> 10:22.260
[chuckles]

10:22.360 --> 10:25.423
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

10:25.523 --> 10:31.130
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:35.334 --> 10:38.238
<i>[The Faces' "Ooh La La"]</i>

10:38.338 --> 10:44.565
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:47.188 --> 10:50.091
<i>♪ Poor old Granddad ♪</i>

10:50.191 --> 10:53.455
<i>♪ I laughed at all his words ♪</i>

10:53.555 --> 10:56.498
<i>♪ I thought he was</i>
<i>a bitter man ♪</i>

10:56.598 --> 10:59.822
<i>♪ He spoke of women's ways ♪</i>

10:59.922 --> 11:01.384
<i>♪ They'll trap you ♪</i>

11:01.484 --> 11:06.069
<i>♪ Then they use you,</i>
<i>before you even know ♪</i>

11:06.169 --> 11:09.313
<i>♪ For love is blind,</i>
<i>and you're far too kind ♪</i>

11:09.413 --> 11:12.476
<i>♪ Don't ever let it show ♪</i>

11:12.576 --> 11:17.241
<i>♪ I wish that I knew</i>
<i>what I know now ♪</i>

11:17.341 --> 11:18.803
<i>♪ When I was younger ♪</i>

11:18.903 --> 11:23.889
<i>♪ I wish that I knew</i>
<i>what I know now ♪</i>

11:23.989 --> 11:25.531
<i>♪ When I was stronger ♪</i>

11:25.631 --> 11:28.534
<i>♪ The can-can,</i>
<i>such a pretty show ♪</i>

11:28.634 --> 11:30.857
<i>♪ Will steal your heart away ♪</i>

11:30.957 --> 11:33.720
[indistinct chatter]

11:35.242 --> 11:36.423
Are we almost there?

11:36.523 --> 11:38.665
'Cause this is a lot of steps.

11:38.765 --> 11:41.228
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:41.328 --> 11:42.990
- Welcome to
the top of the world.

11:43.090 --> 11:46.194
- Wow.
- Oh, it's amazing.

11:46.294 --> 11:47.996
- Wow.
- Whoa.

11:48.096 --> 11:50.098
This is unreal.

11:51.260 --> 11:53.322
Where are we?

11:53.422 --> 11:56.145
Tennessee, this is amazing.

11:57.106 --> 11:59.108
It's incredible.

11:59.829 --> 12:01.611
- Nope. Nope. No.
- Oh.

12:01.711 --> 12:03.714
Whoa.

12:04.955 --> 12:06.096
Wow.

12:06.196 --> 12:07.458
- How high up do
you think we are?

12:07.558 --> 12:10.141
- I--100, maybe, 150 feet.

12:10.241 --> 12:12.243
It's 288 feet.

12:13.404 --> 12:15.547
OK, well, that's, uh, high.

12:15.647 --> 12:17.649
- Maybe Iggy had
the right idea hanging back.

12:18.490 --> 12:21.033
Wait, Max, is Iggy OK?

12:21.133 --> 12:22.515
Why didn't he come?

12:22.615 --> 12:25.438
- He, uh, he just wanted
to be alone for a minute.

12:25.538 --> 12:27.440
I think he's going
through some stuff.

12:27.540 --> 12:31.164
- Yeah, well, he's
missing out on a lot.

12:31.264 --> 12:32.246
Yeah.

12:32.346 --> 12:33.887
All right, so now what?

12:33.987 --> 12:35.810
We're going over the edge.

12:35.910 --> 12:39.254
- We're go-- how's that?

12:39.354 --> 12:41.736
- One by one,
we're going to harness up,

12:41.836 --> 12:44.679
use this belay line to rappel
down the face of the cliff.

12:47.162 --> 12:48.744
Any questions?

12:48.844 --> 12:50.706
Uh, I'll go first.

12:50.806 --> 12:51.707
Are you crazy?

12:51.807 --> 12:53.910
- All I heard
is "I'll go first."

12:54.010 --> 12:57.194
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:57.294 --> 13:00.477
- Cardiopulmonary
bypass initiated.

13:00.577 --> 13:03.240
- Time to stop the heart.
[monitor beeping]

13:03.340 --> 13:06.444
- Core temp is down
to 45 degrees.

13:06.544 --> 13:08.546
- All right.
Here we go.

13:09.668 --> 13:11.169
ACT 466.

13:11.269 --> 13:14.093
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

13:14.193 --> 13:18.818
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:18.918 --> 13:20.780
Wait for it.

13:20.880 --> 13:23.944
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:24.044 --> 13:25.706
[flat tone]

13:25.806 --> 13:28.949
OK, patient is in
suspended animation.

13:29.049 --> 13:30.751
Dr. Nieves, you're up.

13:30.851 --> 13:32.433
Time for you to show off.
You got one hour.

13:32.533 --> 13:33.795
We'll need every second.

13:33.895 --> 13:35.897
Three-hole punch.

13:37.098 --> 13:40.222
[whirring]

13:43.586 --> 13:46.049
- I always thought he
was throwing away his career,

13:46.149 --> 13:48.131
with starting
a family so young.

13:48.231 --> 13:50.894
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:50.994 --> 13:52.996
Now I realise how wrong I was.

13:55.639 --> 13:58.502
And if I can't have it,

13:58.602 --> 14:00.985
least I can do is make sure
he doesn't lose it.

14:01.085 --> 14:02.507
Radiation safety team.

14:02.607 --> 14:03.668
- Hey, hey, hey, get
the hell out of here!

14:03.768 --> 14:05.390
- We are tracking
a radiation spill.

14:05.490 --> 14:06.471
Get the hell out!

14:06.571 --> 14:08.033
We are doing a surgery.

14:08.133 --> 14:11.357
- We discovered our
thallium supply had a leak.

14:11.457 --> 14:13.439
Probably spilled in here.

14:13.539 --> 14:14.801
- Do not come into
the surgical field.

14:14.901 --> 14:16.723
- [beeping]
- Found it! It's in here.

14:16.823 --> 14:18.845
We need everybody
to evacuate immediately.

14:18.945 --> 14:21.088
- My patient has
a blade in his brain.

14:21.188 --> 14:22.529
If we try to move him,
he's dead.

14:22.629 --> 14:24.892
- He also is being
exposed to potentially

14:24.992 --> 14:26.894
lethal amounts of radiation.

14:26.994 --> 14:29.818
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:29.918 --> 14:32.861
Not just the boy,
everybody is being exposed.

14:32.961 --> 14:34.423
- OK.
- Come on.

14:34.523 --> 14:37.847
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:39.288 --> 14:41.190
[falcon calls]

14:41.290 --> 14:43.713
<i>[soft acoustic music]</i>

14:43.813 --> 14:44.714
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:44.814 --> 14:46.396
- All right, people,
here's the deal.

14:46.496 --> 14:48.078
These excursions aren't
just about physically

14:48.178 --> 14:49.560
getting out of the city.

14:49.660 --> 14:50.961
It's about getting away
from the thoughts that

14:51.061 --> 14:52.363
cloud what really matters.

14:52.463 --> 14:54.045
If I stood in the
middle of Fifth Avenue

14:54.145 --> 14:56.327
and I asked people what
their deepest desires were,

14:56.427 --> 14:58.169
I'd probably hear
a lot of people saying

14:58.269 --> 15:00.052
they want to be rich.

15:00.152 --> 15:01.373
That is not what
they really want.

15:01.473 --> 15:02.614
So what do they really want?

15:02.714 --> 15:04.376
Can we speed this up, please?

15:04.476 --> 15:06.098
It's different for everyone.

15:06.198 --> 15:09.062
And in my experience, this
is the best way to find out.

15:09.162 --> 15:11.384
Because when you take a
backwards leap off an almost

15:11.484 --> 15:14.908
300-foot-high cliff, well,

15:15.008 --> 15:17.151
what you really want tends
to become very clear.

15:17.251 --> 15:18.592
Yeah, are we good to go?

15:18.692 --> 15:19.954
- Oh, sounds like
someone's excited

15:20.054 --> 15:21.796
for their first rappel.

15:21.896 --> 15:23.838
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:23.938 --> 15:26.521
- As you're in freefall...
- Yeah.

15:26.621 --> 15:28.924
- Just think about what
you really want in life.

15:29.024 --> 15:32.048
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:32.148 --> 15:33.169
That's it?

15:33.269 --> 15:35.271
We're just going to--

15:36.793 --> 15:38.795
OK, uh...

15:40.957 --> 15:42.960
OK.

15:44.561 --> 15:47.425
<i>[uplifting music]</i>

15:47.525 --> 15:54.453
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:56.174 --> 15:57.436
Oh.

15:57.536 --> 16:00.720
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:00.820 --> 16:01.961
Whoo.

16:02.061 --> 16:03.283
Ahh!

16:03.383 --> 16:10.431
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:20.402 --> 16:26.609
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:27.810 --> 16:29.752
OK, last but not least.

16:29.852 --> 16:31.514
- Yeah.
- Any questions?

16:31.614 --> 16:34.878
- Uh, think I'm ready
as I'll ever be.

16:34.978 --> 16:36.280
- All right,
you know what to do.

16:36.380 --> 16:38.002
Yeah.

16:38.102 --> 16:40.104
OK.

16:40.544 --> 16:42.587
OK. Wait.

16:44.749 --> 16:46.751
What if I don't know
what I want?

16:48.393 --> 16:50.215
Step back and find out.

16:50.315 --> 16:53.179
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

16:53.279 --> 17:00.186
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:00.286 --> 17:02.289
[falcon calls]

17:26.476 --> 17:33.604
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:36.247 --> 17:38.890
[cheering]

17:40.211 --> 17:41.753
I'm a little bit jealous.

17:41.853 --> 17:43.355
- Oh, my God.
- I got to be honest.

17:43.455 --> 17:45.357
It's unbelievable.

17:45.457 --> 17:46.599
Max.

17:46.699 --> 17:48.280
Max, incredible, right?

17:48.380 --> 17:50.383
Yeah, it's incredible.

17:51.384 --> 17:58.512
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:24.621 --> 18:27.705
[wind whooshing]

18:31.389 --> 18:33.391
[grunts]

18:42.081 --> 18:43.703
[screaming]

18:43.803 --> 18:46.846
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:52.292 --> 18:54.315
Hey. Hey.

18:54.415 --> 18:55.997
Oh, my God.

18:56.097 --> 18:57.318
Let's get her on her side.

18:57.418 --> 18:59.420
Easy, easy, easy.

18:59.861 --> 19:01.763
How's her pulse?
Anything?

19:01.863 --> 19:03.805
Starting chest compressions.

19:03.905 --> 19:05.127
- Non-responsive.

19:05.227 --> 19:06.849
A broken femur,
shattered wrist,

19:06.949 --> 19:09.492
possible pelvic fracture.

19:09.592 --> 19:10.853
Max!

19:10.953 --> 19:13.496
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:13.596 --> 19:14.858
- We need an evac.
Call an evac.

19:14.958 --> 19:16.780
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

19:16.880 --> 19:18.342
- Who's got the SAV pump?
- Check around her body.

19:18.442 --> 19:19.663
It might have fallen
out of the bag.

19:19.763 --> 19:21.225
I know she has one.

19:21.325 --> 19:22.226
- OK.
- Oh.

19:22.326 --> 19:23.788
- Got it, got it.
- You got it?

19:23.888 --> 19:25.269
Oh, yeah.

19:25.369 --> 19:28.513
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:28.613 --> 19:29.714
Damn it.

19:29.814 --> 19:30.796
- All right,
try this cell phone.

19:30.896 --> 19:32.898
Yeah, yeah. Give me a sec.

19:33.859 --> 19:35.080
OK, OK.

19:35.180 --> 19:36.922
No, we got
a problem here, guys.

19:37.022 --> 19:38.324
- All right, if we don't get
a rescue helicopter here,

19:38.424 --> 19:39.686
she's got no chance.

19:39.786 --> 19:41.207
- Wait, when was the last time
any of us had service?

19:41.307 --> 19:42.849
- Back where we parked, right?
I'll go back.

19:42.949 --> 19:44.291
I'll go back.

19:44.391 --> 19:45.772
I'll follow the trail.

19:45.872 --> 19:47.775
I'll get-- I'll hit service
before then, probably, right?

19:47.875 --> 19:49.877
[breathing heavily]

19:51.078 --> 19:53.080
What other option do we have?

19:54.482 --> 19:55.864
I'm going. I'm going.

19:55.964 --> 19:59.768
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:02.051 --> 20:03.793
- These protective
lead shields were

20:03.893 --> 20:05.795
designed for X-rays
and should offer you

20:05.895 --> 20:08.398
some protection in here.

20:08.498 --> 20:10.160
Closing sutures.

20:10.260 --> 20:11.641
- You need to put this on,
Dr. Reynolds.

20:11.741 --> 20:12.843
Not going to happen.

20:12.943 --> 20:13.864
I'm not going to
compromise my mobility.

20:13.944 --> 20:15.005
- You're risking
further exposure.

20:15.105 --> 20:16.687
- I don't care.
The patient comes first.

20:16.787 --> 20:20.531
This particular patient
is too important, all right?

20:20.631 --> 20:22.894
Is it really necessary
to clear the observation deck?

20:22.994 --> 20:25.137
- Thallium is an airborne
radioactive substance.

20:25.237 --> 20:27.239
We clear the area.
That's protocol.

20:29.281 --> 20:32.064
This is the last operating
room running on this floor,

20:32.164 --> 20:34.787
so I would strongly advise you
and your team to find a way--

20:34.887 --> 20:36.790
There isn't one!

20:36.890 --> 20:39.513
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:39.613 --> 20:40.754
All done here.

20:40.854 --> 20:42.116
Surgical reconstruction
complete.

20:42.216 --> 20:43.998
- You and your
team need to exit the zone.

20:44.098 --> 20:46.360
- This way, please.
- Show-off.

20:46.460 --> 20:47.602
Good luck, Floyd.

20:47.702 --> 20:50.365
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

20:50.465 --> 20:53.368
- All right, begin reperfusion
and rewarming.

20:53.468 --> 20:54.690
Reperfusion started.

20:54.790 --> 20:57.773
- Dr. Reynolds, these
dosimeters measure exposure.

20:57.873 --> 20:59.695
The second any
of them starts beeping,

20:59.795 --> 21:01.377
we need to pull you out,
no argument.

21:01.477 --> 21:02.779
Fine, let me work.

21:02.879 --> 21:05.222
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:05.322 --> 21:07.324
Gonna have you back in no time.

21:10.167 --> 21:12.910
[breathing heavily]

21:13.010 --> 21:15.914
<i>[tense music]</i>

21:16.014 --> 21:20.559
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:20.659 --> 21:23.021
[panting]

21:24.503 --> 21:26.505
OK.

21:30.029 --> 21:32.372
[cracking, rustling]

21:32.472 --> 21:34.474
[falcon calls]

21:37.958 --> 21:39.380
Hello?

21:39.480 --> 21:42.263
[rustling]

21:42.363 --> 21:45.827
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:45.927 --> 21:47.509
[grunts]

21:47.609 --> 21:50.412
[breathing heavily]

21:54.297 --> 21:56.279
Hello?

21:56.379 --> 21:58.381
[twig snaps]

22:10.955 --> 22:12.958
Hey.

22:13.919 --> 22:15.921
Hi.

22:17.483 --> 22:19.825
Uh, I'm Iggy.

22:19.925 --> 22:21.627
Are you OK?

22:21.727 --> 22:23.309
Just lost.

22:23.409 --> 22:25.412
Are you OK?

22:26.292 --> 22:28.355
Yeah. Yeah, I'm OK.

22:28.455 --> 22:29.476
I just-- I fell.

22:29.576 --> 22:31.038
It's nothing.

22:31.138 --> 22:33.160
- My family
is out here camping.

22:33.260 --> 22:35.263
I just got separated from them.

22:36.144 --> 22:37.525
OK, but they're nearby?

22:37.625 --> 22:38.927
I don't know.

22:39.027 --> 22:40.889
You lost too?

22:40.989 --> 22:43.652
- No, I'm not lost, I'm, uh--

22:43.752 --> 22:45.694
no, I'm looking for cell
service, but I got to--

22:45.794 --> 22:46.856
I got to keep going, so--

22:46.956 --> 22:48.177
Can I come with you?

22:48.277 --> 22:50.700
Then you can call
my parents too.

22:50.800 --> 22:52.802
Can you run?

22:53.643 --> 22:55.145
OK, come on.

22:55.245 --> 22:58.349
<i>[tense music]</i>

22:58.449 --> 23:00.911
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:01.011 --> 23:02.513
- What is that?
- Smart AED.

23:02.613 --> 23:04.956
It uses the phone's battery
as a charge.

23:05.056 --> 23:07.359
I got it the last time
Vanessa OD'd.

23:07.459 --> 23:08.480
OK.

23:08.580 --> 23:10.322
This one goes here.

23:10.422 --> 23:12.725
[AED whirs]

23:12.825 --> 23:14.647
OK, clear.

23:14.747 --> 23:16.289
[beeps]

23:16.389 --> 23:18.611
[shock]

23:18.711 --> 23:20.453
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

23:20.553 --> 23:22.556
Going again.

23:22.956 --> 23:24.578
[beep, shock]

23:24.678 --> 23:29.303
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:29.403 --> 23:31.025
- Slow but steady.
She's alive.

23:31.125 --> 23:33.328
[rocks crumbling]

23:37.052 --> 23:38.273
This rock face is unstable.

23:38.373 --> 23:39.435
We got to get her out of here.

23:39.535 --> 23:40.636
Let's move these.

23:40.736 --> 23:43.639
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

23:43.739 --> 23:45.982
[loud grunting]

23:47.143 --> 23:48.165
[stammers] There's no way.

23:48.265 --> 23:49.526
They're too heavy.

23:49.626 --> 23:50.567
- It's bedrock,
it's not going to move.

23:50.667 --> 23:52.730
She's wedged in.

23:52.830 --> 23:54.051
[mouthing words]

23:54.151 --> 23:55.973
Her rhythm is unstable.

23:56.073 --> 23:58.136
- Her body is going
in and out of shock.

23:58.236 --> 24:00.819
- What if Iggy doesn't
make it in time?

24:00.919 --> 24:02.100
We need to build a fire.

24:02.200 --> 24:03.221
- The smoke could
draw attention.

24:03.321 --> 24:04.623
I'll help you.

24:04.723 --> 24:10.409
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:12.091 --> 24:13.513
Come on.

24:13.613 --> 24:15.615
Oh, God.

24:16.777 --> 24:18.278
You move fast.

24:18.378 --> 24:21.482
- Yeah, I'm, uh, I'm worried
about it getting dark.

24:21.582 --> 24:23.444
Work out a lot?

24:23.544 --> 24:24.645
I try.

24:24.745 --> 24:26.087
Good for you.

24:26.187 --> 24:27.449
My family loves exercise.

24:27.549 --> 24:30.132
I just really never
gotten into it.

24:30.232 --> 24:31.733
Worried you're
going the wrong way?

24:31.833 --> 24:33.455
My sense of direction is awful.

24:33.555 --> 24:35.177
My brother says
if I have two choices,

24:35.277 --> 24:37.140
I should choose one
and go the other way,

24:37.240 --> 24:39.462
but he's also kind of douche.

24:39.562 --> 24:43.266
- Hey, uh, is your
family anywhere nearby?

24:43.366 --> 24:45.589
You think, like--does any
of this look familiar to you?

24:45.689 --> 24:48.713
- I actually need
to tell you something.

24:48.813 --> 24:50.474
I didn't get separated.

24:50.574 --> 24:52.577
I ran away.

24:53.257 --> 24:54.319
Why would you do that?

24:54.419 --> 24:55.720
Don't get snippy.

24:55.820 --> 24:59.124
It's not like you didn't run
away when you were my age.

24:59.224 --> 25:01.607
What are you talking about?

25:01.707 --> 25:03.609
- You ran away
after your dad found you

25:03.709 --> 25:05.692
sneaking a candy bar for
your new secret hiding place

25:05.792 --> 25:07.794
under the porch.

25:08.755 --> 25:11.698
So he slapped you
in the head, hard.

25:11.798 --> 25:13.340
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

25:13.440 --> 25:15.142
And then you ran away.

25:15.242 --> 25:16.984
A couple of hours later,
you wussed out,

25:17.084 --> 25:19.086
and you went right back.

25:19.927 --> 25:22.110
Who are you?

25:22.210 --> 25:23.752
I'm you.

25:23.852 --> 25:26.575
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:28.857 --> 25:30.079
This is all my fault.

25:30.179 --> 25:31.481
- It's your fault that
our guide's anchor

25:31.581 --> 25:33.843
broke free from the mountain?

25:33.943 --> 25:36.006
- We're only here because I
was trying to avoid Helen.

25:36.106 --> 25:38.368
- Tennessee would
be here either way.

25:38.468 --> 25:41.372
Only with a bunch
of tax accountants.

25:41.472 --> 25:43.694
- Look, she'd be dead
if we weren't here,

25:43.794 --> 25:45.796
and so would they.

25:46.517 --> 25:48.740
So, thank God you're
avoiding Helen.

25:48.840 --> 25:50.222
Clearly, the right move.

25:50.322 --> 25:52.324
- Give me that.
- OK.

25:55.888 --> 25:57.310
Done this before?

25:57.410 --> 25:59.512
- Jewish summer camp,
when I wasn't sneaking off

25:59.612 --> 26:01.614
- to smoke with the boys.
- Mm.

26:05.819 --> 26:09.563
- You know, for months
after she left--

26:09.663 --> 26:13.828
for months, I would have done
anything to see her, anything.

26:16.151 --> 26:18.293
Just to ask her why.

26:18.393 --> 26:21.216
<i>[somber music]</i>

26:21.316 --> 26:22.778
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:22.878 --> 26:24.901
I used dream of this moment.

26:25.001 --> 26:31.708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:31.808 --> 26:34.151
- You're doing
the right thing, Max.

26:34.251 --> 26:35.512
Look, you going to see Helen,

26:35.612 --> 26:38.235
it would be like me
going to see

26:38.335 --> 26:39.757
a hundred milligrams
of Adderall.

26:39.857 --> 26:41.859
[chuckles]

26:42.700 --> 26:47.366
- Whatever she has to say,
it's not gonna help.

26:47.466 --> 26:51.510
Just keep looking forward,
not behind.

26:57.797 --> 26:59.820
- Think I'll take that
as a sign.

26:59.920 --> 27:01.782
[loud rumbling]

27:01.882 --> 27:03.884
What was that?

27:06.968 --> 27:09.791
<i>[tense music]</i>

27:09.891 --> 27:12.234
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:12.334 --> 27:14.336
Rock slide.

27:18.541 --> 27:18.701
.

27:18.781 --> 27:21.484
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

27:21.584 --> 27:22.645
I've got Ben.

27:22.745 --> 27:24.367
Yeah, I got Tennessee.

27:24.467 --> 27:25.448
Stop, stop.

27:25.548 --> 27:27.451
This whole side
is going to fall.

27:27.551 --> 27:29.373
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:29.473 --> 27:31.475
Don't!

27:31.836 --> 27:33.457
Just go.

27:33.557 --> 27:36.321
[grunting]

27:40.005 --> 27:42.007
[coughs]

27:44.570 --> 27:46.572
I need you to listen to me.

27:48.374 --> 27:50.376
We got to get you out of here.

27:52.258 --> 27:54.281
I got to get you out of here.

27:54.381 --> 27:56.924
There's only one way
to do that.

27:57.024 --> 27:58.926
[breathing heavily]

27:59.026 --> 28:01.169
My foot.

28:01.269 --> 28:02.770
No. Please, no.

28:02.870 --> 28:04.612
- The rockslide will kill you.
It's the only way.

28:04.712 --> 28:06.895
Tennessee, look at me.

28:06.995 --> 28:08.377
It's the only way.

28:08.477 --> 28:12.221
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:12.321 --> 28:13.983
OK.

28:14.083 --> 28:16.085
- OK.
- My bag.

28:18.488 --> 28:19.950
In here.

28:20.050 --> 28:26.977
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:36.108 --> 28:37.129
[grunts]

28:37.229 --> 28:39.572
Bite down on this.

28:39.672 --> 28:42.655
[whimpering]

28:42.755 --> 28:44.978
- [groans]
- Hold her steady.

28:45.078 --> 28:47.841
[sobbing]

28:49.363 --> 28:51.145
OK.

28:51.245 --> 28:53.247
Look at me.

28:54.208 --> 28:55.269
It's OK.

28:55.369 --> 28:56.511
Here.

28:56.611 --> 28:59.414
[screaming in pain]

29:00.455 --> 29:03.318
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

29:03.418 --> 29:05.321
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:05.421 --> 29:07.423
OK.

29:08.104 --> 29:09.245
Are you ready?

29:09.345 --> 29:13.610
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:13.710 --> 29:17.154
[screaming, echoes]

29:21.759 --> 29:23.982
- Did I hit my head?
- You wish.

29:24.082 --> 29:26.945
That would mean you don't
have huge emotional issues.

29:27.045 --> 29:30.068
- You're not real, and I don't
have huge emotional issues.

29:30.168 --> 29:31.510
Yeah, right.

29:31.610 --> 29:34.874
You can't even tell your
friends how sad you are.

29:34.974 --> 29:36.355
I don't have time for this.

29:36.455 --> 29:38.198
- Oh, like you don't have time
to sign your divorce papers?

29:38.298 --> 29:39.719
I'm not going to.

29:39.819 --> 29:41.361
I'm gonna ask Martin
for another chance.

29:41.461 --> 29:43.163
- Come on, we both know
that's not going to happen.

29:43.263 --> 29:46.046
Plus, you dumped him,
which frankly blows my mind,

29:46.146 --> 29:47.328
because he's super hot.

29:47.428 --> 29:48.569
Like, I'm psyched to meet him.

29:48.669 --> 29:50.571
- You'll understand
when you're older.

29:50.671 --> 29:54.296
True love is
worth fighting for.

29:54.396 --> 29:56.218
I had to leave because I
had to figure out who I was.

29:56.318 --> 29:57.579
I did that.

29:57.679 --> 29:59.942
Now I can go back.

30:00.042 --> 30:01.464
Classic us.

30:01.564 --> 30:03.146
Running away and going back.

30:03.246 --> 30:04.827
Why did you go back?

30:04.927 --> 30:07.751
I mean, you ran away, hung
out in a park for four hours,

30:07.851 --> 30:08.952
and then you went
right back,

30:09.052 --> 30:10.233
even though nothing had
changed.

30:10.333 --> 30:11.995
Like, what's the point?

30:12.095 --> 30:14.518
Uh...

30:14.618 --> 30:16.621
I don't know.

30:17.421 --> 30:19.364
It wasn't all bad.

30:19.464 --> 30:21.546
It wasn't.

30:23.348 --> 30:25.390
I missed my mom.

30:26.351 --> 30:30.796
I, uh, I missed my brother when
he wasn't being a jerk to me.

30:32.078 --> 30:35.722
I didn't want to say goodbye
to those things forever.

30:37.684 --> 30:40.227
Eventually, you did leave.

30:40.327 --> 30:41.989
Never came back.

30:42.089 --> 30:46.114
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:46.214 --> 30:48.216
Yeah.

30:49.057 --> 30:52.100
I realised that was the price
of a better life.

30:54.103 --> 30:56.405
Sometimes it's scary to walk
away from the good things,

30:56.505 --> 30:59.589
but you have to.

31:01.191 --> 31:03.974
It's what you have to do
to move forward.

31:04.074 --> 31:06.136
- That's the funny thing
about being lost.

31:06.236 --> 31:08.779
Clearly it's not about
knowing your way forward.

31:08.879 --> 31:11.302
It's knowing that the
answer isn't looking back.

31:11.402 --> 31:18.290
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:28.181 --> 31:30.183
[phone chimes]

31:34.788 --> 31:37.872
[phone chiming]

31:39.393 --> 31:42.257
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

31:42.357 --> 31:49.245
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:52.448 --> 31:54.450
[grunts]

31:57.414 --> 31:58.715
Got it.

31:58.815 --> 31:59.877
All right, let's get her up.

31:59.977 --> 32:01.438
Easy. Watch her head.

32:01.538 --> 32:04.322
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:04.422 --> 32:05.563
Got her?

32:05.663 --> 32:07.685
OK, you're doing great.

32:07.785 --> 32:09.567
[rocks crashing]

32:09.667 --> 32:10.889
- You're doing great,
Tennessee.

32:10.989 --> 32:12.991
- Keep moving!
Keep moving!

32:14.313 --> 32:18.858
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:18.958 --> 32:20.380
Max, there's too much blood.

32:20.480 --> 32:22.021
- All right, all right,
set her down, set her down.

32:22.121 --> 32:24.264
Easy, easy.

32:24.364 --> 32:26.066
How's she doing?

32:26.166 --> 32:27.868
Fast and weak.

32:27.968 --> 32:29.790
- All right, she's going
to go into hypovolemic shock

32:29.890 --> 32:30.951
unless we tighten
the tourniquet.

32:31.051 --> 32:32.233
It's soaked through.

32:32.333 --> 32:33.675
- Uh--

32:33.775 --> 32:36.598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:36.698 --> 32:38.240
[mouthing words]

32:38.340 --> 32:39.401
Yeah, she's right.

32:39.501 --> 32:41.503
We need to cauterise her leg.

32:41.904 --> 32:43.285
We have the fire.

32:43.385 --> 32:44.487
- We don't have--

32:44.587 --> 32:46.589
Metal. We need metal.

32:48.191 --> 32:50.193
A carabiner?

32:51.595 --> 32:53.096
It's going to have to do.

32:53.196 --> 32:54.618
- All right, we got
to get him off bypass.

32:54.718 --> 32:55.819
What's the core temp?

32:55.919 --> 32:58.823
[dosimeter beeping]

32:58.923 --> 33:01.185
- You need to step
out of the OR.

33:01.285 --> 33:02.707
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

33:02.807 --> 33:03.828
Now!

33:03.928 --> 33:06.271
Core temp is 98.6.

33:06.371 --> 33:07.513
[beeping continues]

33:07.613 --> 33:09.435
OK. Come on.

33:09.535 --> 33:11.237
Let's go. Follow me.

33:11.337 --> 33:13.800
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:13.900 --> 33:17.023
Ready, Dr. Reynolds.

33:18.665 --> 33:20.207
OK.

33:20.307 --> 33:21.448
We're going to take him
off bypass.

33:21.548 --> 33:23.130
Suture?

33:23.230 --> 33:25.172
Good. All right.

33:25.272 --> 33:29.297
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:29.397 --> 33:31.179
Get those paddles ready.

33:31.279 --> 33:32.821
All right,
restarting the heart.

33:32.921 --> 33:35.464
[flatlining]

33:35.564 --> 33:37.186
Charging.

33:37.286 --> 33:38.988
Clear.
[shocks]

33:39.088 --> 33:41.671
[flatlining continues]

33:41.771 --> 33:42.712
OK, going again.

33:42.812 --> 33:44.814
Charging, clear.

33:47.217 --> 33:48.599
Going again.

33:48.699 --> 33:50.701
Charging, clear.

33:51.942 --> 33:53.124
[dosimeter beeping]

33:53.224 --> 33:54.806
- Dr. Reynolds, you need
to step out of the OR.

33:54.906 --> 33:56.167
Going again. Charge.

33:56.267 --> 33:57.328
[shocks]

33:57.428 --> 33:59.291
- Dr. Reynolds,
you need to leave.

33:59.391 --> 34:01.393
Come on.

34:02.154 --> 34:03.575
- You shocked the heart
four times.

34:03.675 --> 34:04.897
Three times is protocol.

34:04.997 --> 34:06.178
- You need to come with me.
- Come on.

34:06.278 --> 34:07.019
Come on.

34:07.119 --> 34:08.821
The patient is unresponsive!

34:08.921 --> 34:10.143
- Not going to lose you.
Not going to lose you.

34:10.243 --> 34:11.324
- You've been exposed
to high levels of radiation.

34:11.404 --> 34:12.706
You need to come
with us right now.

34:12.806 --> 34:14.348
Come on. Damn it!

34:14.448 --> 34:17.391
<i>[tense music]</i>

34:17.491 --> 34:18.712
OK.

34:18.812 --> 34:20.434
All right, hold her.

34:20.534 --> 34:22.797
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:22.897 --> 34:24.439
Hold her tight.

34:24.539 --> 34:29.825
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:30.946 --> 34:32.948
[screaming]

34:37.193 --> 34:38.415
He's not going to die today.

34:38.515 --> 34:39.656
Intracardiac epi.

34:39.756 --> 34:41.698
- On it.
[flatlining]

34:41.798 --> 34:44.181
Inject just above my fingers.

34:44.281 --> 34:46.283
One milligram epi in.

34:47.244 --> 34:49.107
Dr. Reynolds, call it.

34:49.207 --> 34:51.309
Come on, come on, come on.

34:51.409 --> 34:53.832
- There's nothing more
you can do.

34:53.932 --> 34:55.193
Get yourself to safety.

34:55.293 --> 34:56.475
Wait a minute, wait.

34:56.575 --> 34:57.476
Dr. Reynolds, call it!

34:57.576 --> 34:59.038
Wait a second.

34:59.138 --> 35:00.840
I got something.

35:00.940 --> 35:02.522
Yeah, I got something.

35:02.622 --> 35:04.564
[monitor beeping]

35:04.664 --> 35:05.685
Oh, my God.

35:05.785 --> 35:10.370
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:10.470 --> 35:13.134
- All right, get him
to a new OR, now.

35:13.234 --> 35:15.696
[people chattering frantically]

35:15.796 --> 35:21.683
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:23.886 --> 35:26.569
[fire crackling]

35:31.935 --> 35:33.937
[sighs]

35:41.665 --> 35:43.808
[no speech]

35:43.908 --> 35:46.771
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

35:46.871 --> 35:53.959
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:57.643 --> 35:59.646
[sighs]

36:04.171 --> 36:11.219
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:17.185 --> 36:19.188
[whispering]

36:32.042 --> 36:37.328
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:51.184 --> 36:54.267
[helicopter whirring]

36:56.710 --> 36:58.712
Lauren.

37:01.916 --> 37:04.559
[whirring amplifies]

37:06.641 --> 37:07.662
Over here!

37:07.762 --> 37:09.384
Hey!

37:09.484 --> 37:10.866
Hey!

37:10.966 --> 37:12.988
Over here!

37:13.088 --> 37:15.030
Hey!

37:15.130 --> 37:17.133
Hey!

37:20.617 --> 37:22.619
Iggy did it!

37:25.582 --> 37:28.165
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:28.265 --> 37:29.727
<i>Hey, Floyd.</i>

37:29.827 --> 37:32.109
<i>Thank you. Thank you.</i>

37:34.953 --> 37:38.016
<i>Floyd, my oldest friend.</i>

37:38.116 --> 37:40.499
<i>[laughs]</i>

37:40.599 --> 37:42.601
<i>Thank you for saving</i>
<i>my family.</i>

37:44.283 --> 37:46.406
<i>Consider the car debt repaid.</i>

37:48.968 --> 37:50.190
<i>Thank you.</i>

37:50.290 --> 37:52.993
<i>[tender music]</i>

37:53.093 --> 37:58.159
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:58.259 --> 38:01.402
- Um, I'm--

38:01.502 --> 38:04.706
I'm sorry, the radiation
has got me all, uh--

38:06.989 --> 38:08.991
I just--

38:10.192 --> 38:13.056
It's just between, uh,
you know,

38:13.156 --> 38:16.539
this and you leaving.

38:16.639 --> 38:18.662
- Why do you act like
everything

38:18.762 --> 38:20.764
is over and done with?

38:22.806 --> 38:25.770
- It's 'cause you're leaving
in six days.

38:27.852 --> 38:29.234
Yes.

38:29.334 --> 38:32.197
Only 'cause you never
asked me to stay.

38:32.297 --> 38:39.385
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:49.036 --> 38:50.177
Iggy, hey.

38:50.277 --> 38:51.619
You OK?

38:51.719 --> 38:52.940
Hey.

38:53.040 --> 38:54.262
Yeah, yeah, fine.

38:54.362 --> 38:56.264
I'm just embarrassed, mostly.

38:56.364 --> 38:58.106
- What were you doing up
on a mountain?

38:58.206 --> 39:01.790
Um, I was gaining clarity.

39:01.890 --> 39:04.914
<i>[Joe Purdy's "Miss Me"]</i>

39:05.014 --> 39:07.957
I, uh--I signed
the divorce papers.

39:08.057 --> 39:09.719
- We don't need to worry
about that right now.

39:09.819 --> 39:10.840
Yes. Yes, we do.

39:10.940 --> 39:12.282
Yes, we do.

39:12.382 --> 39:15.245
Because I have been, um--

39:15.345 --> 39:17.128
I've been having a really
hard time accepting

39:17.228 --> 39:20.131
that what we had is over.

39:20.231 --> 39:24.095
But sometimes
to move forward,

39:24.195 --> 39:27.199
you have to leave
something behind.

39:28.560 --> 39:30.503
Our marriage is over.

39:30.603 --> 39:32.985
I am certain of that now.

39:33.085 --> 39:38.471
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:38.571 --> 39:40.674
You seem pretty OK with it.

39:40.774 --> 39:42.776
Yeah.

39:43.377 --> 39:44.598
Because I finally
know the direction

39:44.698 --> 39:46.040
that I want to be headed in.

39:46.140 --> 39:50.245
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:50.345 --> 39:56.492
Martin, will you go
on a date with me?

39:56.592 --> 39:58.574
<i>♪ Walk out the door ♪</i>

39:58.674 --> 40:02.859
<i>♪ And I bet you ain't got</i>
<i>nothing left to learn ♪</i>

40:02.959 --> 40:07.184
<i>♪ It's better that way 'cause</i>
<i>you never get burned ♪</i>

40:07.284 --> 40:12.350
<i>♪ And you try not to think</i>
<i>about what might have been ♪</i>

40:12.450 --> 40:16.474
<i>♪ 'Cause you know this town</i>
<i>is just sink or swim ♪</i>

40:16.574 --> 40:18.677
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

40:18.777 --> 40:21.199
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

40:21.299 --> 40:23.042
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

40:23.142 --> 40:25.144
Vanessa, Vanessa.

40:27.306 --> 40:28.608
I'm really sorry.

40:28.708 --> 40:30.710
I thought you were
someone else.

40:32.993 --> 40:38.219
Wait, um, I'm Lauren.

40:38.319 --> 40:40.381
I'm three years sober.

40:40.481 --> 40:43.805
And there's a seat right
next to me if you want it.

40:46.848 --> 40:48.890
- Why do you care
what happens to me?

40:50.652 --> 40:54.357
- Because today
I asked the universe

40:54.457 --> 40:57.280
to let me help someone...

40:57.380 --> 40:59.582
who used to be just like me.

41:01.985 --> 41:08.873
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:18.003 --> 41:20.426
<i>- ♪ Now I hear</i>
<i>you're in love ♪</i>

41:20.526 --> 41:22.428
<i>♪ With some big city man ♪</i>

41:22.528 --> 41:27.234
<i>♪ And together you're making</i>
<i>your big city plans ♪</i>

41:27.334 --> 41:31.839
<i>♪ And you hope he don't</i>
<i>find out about who you are ♪</i>

41:31.939 --> 41:36.924
<i>♪ That we used to catch</i>
<i>fireflies in mason jars ♪</i>

41:37.024 --> 41:41.129
<i>♪ And we used to go down</i>
<i>to the county fair ♪</i>

41:41.229 --> 41:45.814
<i>♪ And we listened to</i>
<i>bluegrass in summer air ♪</i>

41:45.914 --> 41:50.259
<i>♪ And we danced all night</i>
<i>as the rain came down ♪</i>

41:50.359 --> 41:54.985
<i>♪ And you held my hand as</i>
<i>we slept on the ground ♪</i>

41:55.085 --> 41:59.430
<i>♪ And we wrote our names</i>
<i>in the old oak wood ♪</i>

41:59.530 --> 42:04.816
<i>♪ I guess some things don't</i>
<i>work out like they should ♪</i>

42:06.458 --> 42:09.201
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

42:09.301 --> 42:11.323
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

42:11.423 --> 42:13.986
[mouthing words]

42:19.672 --> 42:24.738
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:24.838 --> 42:27.301
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

42:27.401 --> 42:29.584
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

42:29.684 --> 42:31.826
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

42:31.926 --> 42:33.868
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

42:33.968 --> 42:36.712
<i>♪ Do you miss me, yeah ♪</i>

42:36.812 --> 42:38.514
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

42:38.614 --> 42:40.876
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>

42:40.976 --> 42:43.900
<i>♪ Do you miss me? ♪</i>
